Preheat your oven to 200°C. Place a few potatoes at a time in between two #wooden spoon{} handles. Make slices widthways at 3mm intervals, making sure not to cut the whole way through. Repeat with the remaining @Salad Potatoes{350}. Put the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and tender, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Trim the @Green Beans{150} then chop into half. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from the fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #small saucepan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, add the shallot and cook until soft, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add the @Water for the Sauce{150}(ml) and @Chicken Stock Paste{10}. Bring to the boil and cook until reduced by half, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the @Creme Fraiche{75}, bring to the boil and remove the #pan from the heat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with salt and pepper. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate, cover with #foil and allow to rest for a couple of minutes.

Once the steak is out of the pan, wipe out the pan with #kitchen paper{}. Pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Add the beans, season with salt and pepper, then stir-fry until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water and cover to steam them if needed.

Pour any resting juices from the steak into the sauce along with half of the @Truffle Zest{1}(split). Stir well and reheat until piping hot. Thinly slice the steak and share between your #plates. Serve with the hasselback potatoes and beans alongside. Drizzle over the sauce and sprinkle over the remaining truffle zest. Enjoy!